Wow, I stand out from the rest of the crowd like yeah
But ain't got to play ball to hear your cheer in the crowd

Shitting on these niggas, like a movement from my bowels
People want to know how it feels in the clouds
But I guess they'll never know, 'cause I'm never coming down
I started with a dream, added a little faith
And mixed it with adversity and let it marinate
I put it in the oven for a while, let it bake (Yeah)
Call it food for thought, put it on your plate (Eat)
I'm from the mighty Motown, home sweet home
Where I roam like a phone, in an unknown zone
My niggas roam like a phone in an unknown zone

And I'm so low

Why they local like they old schools
